# allowed-signers — trust anchor for optional commit-signature verification.
#
# Off by default. To enable: set PANTOKEN_VERIFY_SIGNATURES=true in
# ~/.local/state/pantoken/pantoken.env, then list the SSH public key(s) you sign commits
# with below (one per line). auto-deploy.sh points git's
# gpg.ssh.allowedSignersFile here and refuses to deploy any new commit on
# origin/main that isn't signed by a listed key.
#
# Format (the principal must match your committer email; namespaces=git is required):
#   timo.freiberg@gmail.com namespaces="git" ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3Nz...your-key
#
# Find your signing key:  cat ~/.ssh/id_ed25519.pub   (or whatever `git config user.signingkey` points to)
